{
  "doc_id": "16123",
  "text": "While there is significant evidence that microglia can contribute to the initiation and/or progression of AD pathology it's also clear that they can have beneficial effects. In animal models of AD it has been shown that impairment of microglial phagocytic activity accelerates pathology progression [CITATION_1] whereas exogenous supplementation of microglia favours clearance of Ab plaques [CITATION_2] . Similarly, post mortem follow up of patients who took part in a clinical trial of Ab peptide immunisation revealed evidence of extensive phagocytic clearance of Ab from the cortex [CITATION_3] .",
